==Finnish==

===Etymology===
From Proto-Finnish ''*-kme'', where the ''k'' is marker for the present tense. In the past tense, there was originally ''i'' in place of ''k'' (''*-ime'') but the present suffix has been generalized to all tenses and moods. The ''*-me'' part is probably identical to the first person plural pronoun ''[[me|me#Finnish]]'' and has probably ended in a consonant.

===Personal suffix===
'''-mme'''

# Forms the first person plural of verbs.

====Usage====
Suffixed to the same stem that the first person singular has both in the present and the past tense, and in all moods.

Colloquially, the indefinite person is used instead of the actual first person plural. See [[-an]] and [[-in]].

